                <note rend="inline" type="source">314.115C43/148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-08T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >August 8, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. Referring to the Department’s telegram of August 7, 2 p.m. The Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs orally joined in the selection of the Chief Justice of British
                    Honduras and agrees that he sit at Belize.</p>
                <p>The Minister suggests that the Department and the Guatemalan Minister in
                    Washington ascertain through the British Embassy whether the Chief Justice
                    accepts. He suggests that if the Chief <pb facs="0264" n="146" xml:id="pg_146"/>
                    Justice does not accept some Cuban could perhaps be agreed upon because of
                    proximity.</p>
                <p>The Minister agrees that a decision regarding the honorarium be deferred.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geissler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
